longBusinessSummary: Musk Metals Corp. engages in the acquisition, exploration, and development of mineral properties in Canada. The company holds a 100% undivided interest in the Pluto Gold and Base Metals Property that comprises of 58 claims covering an area of approximately 3,223 hectares. It also holds an agreement to acquire a 100% interest in the Elon Lithium property that covers an area of approximately 245 hectares located in the La Corne and Fiedmont townships of Quebec; and a 100% interest in the Pakeagama Lithium property that consists of four mining claims covering an area of approximately 1,490 hectares located in northwestern Ontario. The company was formerly known as Gold Plus Mining Inc. and changed its name to Musk Metals Corp. in March 2021. Musk Metals Corp. is headquartered in Vancouver, British Columbia.
